The Twilio MCP server allows AI coding agents to access Twilio's API surface and documentation directly within an IDE or agent [1][2]. It indexes public OpenAPI specifications across 30+ products, eliminating the need for web scraping or manual documentation lookups [1][2].

There are two primary ways to access this:
1. Hosted Server: For documentation and API schema retrieval only (no authentication required), point your IDE to https://mcp.twilio.com/docs [1].
2. Alpha MCP Server: For executing API calls, use the `@twilio-alpha/mcp` package [3][4].

To configure the Alpha server in your client:
```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "twilio": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": [
        "-y",
        "@twilio-alpha/mcp",
        "YOUR_ACCOUNT_SID/YOUR_API_KEY:YOUR_API_SECRET",
        "--services",
        "twilio_api_v2010"
      ]
    }
  }
}
```
Because of LLM context limits, use `--services` and `--tags` to filter the tools [3][5]. Note that the Alpha server is a beta tool that may increase token costs due to context caching [2][6].
